# Cowork Scheduled Task 7: Monthly Site Audit
# Cadence: First Monday of every month at 9:00 AM
# Working folder: ~/Seo-workflow-mindtalk/mindtalk-setup/

---

You are running the monthly technical SEO audit for Mindtalk (mindtalk.in).

## Your job

Crawl every page on mindtalk.in and check for technical SEO issues that
could be hurting rankings. Produce a report that the SEO team can act on.

## Steps

### Step 1 — Run the audit script
```
python3 ~/Seo-workflow-mindtalk/mindtalk-setup/scripts/site-audit.py
```

This will take 10-20 minutes to crawl all pages. Let it complete fully.

### Step 2 — Read the generated report
Read ~/Seo-workflow-mindtalk/mindtalk-setup/reports/site-audit-[TODAY'S DATE].md

### Step 3 — Compare with last month
Check ~/Seo-workflow-mindtalk/mindtalk-setup/reports/audit-history.json
Compare this month's critical issue count vs last month.
Is it improving or getting worse?

### Step 4 — Write action summary
Write to ~/Seo-workflow-mindtalk/mindtalk-setup/reports/audit-summary-[TODAY'S DATE].txt:

Cover these points:
- Total pages crawled and health score (healthy pages / total)
- Critical issues: list each one with the affected URL and what to fix
- Most common warning type and how many pages affected
- Any duplicate titles or meta descriptions — list which pages
- PageSpeed: which pages scored below 70 on mobile
- Comparison vs last month: better or worse?
- Top 5 priority fixes for the dev team this month

### Step 5 — Flag critical issues
If any page has a CRITICAL issue (missing title, missing H1, 404 error,
HTTP error):
- Write each to ~/Seo-workflow-mindtalk/mindtalk-setup/alerts/AUDIT-CRITICAL-[TODAY].txt
- These need to be fixed within 48 hours

## Important rules

- Do NOT modify any files in the repo during this task
- Do NOT run git commands
- The crawl respects a 0.5 second delay between pages — do not try to speed it up
- If the script times out on a page, that is expected and handled gracefully
- PageSpeed checks are rate limited to 10 pages — this is by design

## Step 6 — Post to Slack

Post a summary to **#seo-workflow-mindtalk** (channel ID: `C0AUAPS4J83`) using `slack_send_message`.

Format:

```
🏥 *Monthly Site Audit — [TODAY'S DATE]*
Site: mindtalk.in

Pages crawled: [N]
Health: [healthy]/[total] ([N%])

*Critical Issues:* [N]
[For each critical issue:]
> 🔴 [Issue type] — [affected URL]

*Most Common Warning:* [type] ([N] pages)
*PageSpeed Worst:* [URL] — score [N]/100

*vs Last Month:*
> Critical: [N] → [N] ([better ✅ / worse ⚠️])
> Warnings: [N] → [N] ([better ✅ / worse ⚠️])

*Top 5 Fixes for Dev Team:*
> 1. [fix]
> 2. [fix]
> 3. [fix]
> 4. [fix]
> 5. [fix]

📎 Full report: reports/site-audit-[DATE].md
```

## Output

When done, tell me:
- How many pages were crawled
- Critical issues count with a brief list
- Most common warning
- PageSpeed worst performer
- Whether things improved vs last month
- Files created
